<workout_file>
  <author>Gravel God Training</author>
  <name>W01 Tue - FTP Test + Aerobic Efficiency</name>
  <description>• STRUCTURE:
  • 30 min warmup
  • 5 min all-out
  • 10 min recovery
  • 20 min max effort
  • 15 min easy
  • 45 min @ 65-70% FTP (monitor HR drift, RPE, fuel efficiency)
  • 15 min cooldown

  • FTP test sets zones.
  • Pace it right—sustained 20 minutes.
  • Then 45-min aerobic efficiency test: hold 65-70% FTP and monitor HR drift, perceived effort, and how fueling feels.
  • Elite athletes have minimal drift.
  • Write everything down.
  • FTP = 20-min × 0.95.
  • Calculate aerobic decoupling: if HR drifts &gt;3-5%, aerobic efficiency needs work.</description>
  <sportType>bike</sportType>
      <workout>
    <Warmup Duration="1800" PowerLow="0.50" PowerHigh="0.75"/>
    <SteadyState Duration="300" Power="1.20"/>
    <SteadyState Duration="600" Power="0.55"/>
    <SteadyState Duration="1200" Power="1.05"/>
    <SteadyState Duration="900" Power="0.55"/>
    <SteadyState Duration="2700" Power="0.68"/>
    <Cooldown Duration="900" PowerLow="0.70" PowerHigh="0.50"/>
  </workout>
